title: Na Tang’s CV
text:
tan22016@byui.edu | My wikipedia page



Brigham Young University–Idaho Jan. 2023 – Present Bachelor of Science in Computer Science GPA: 4.0/4.0


Programming with Functions (Python), Introduction to Computer Science, Algorithmic Thinking, Computer Systems, Web Fundamentals (HTML, CSS), Database, Data Structures



Python, HTML, CSS, MongoDB, MySQL, FastAPI, Git, LaTeX







Developing and deploying a web application using FastAPI to leverage Python’s versatility for API development.
Implementing essential CRUD operations to enhance the application’s capabilities and user interaction.
Utilizing MongoDB for optimizing data storage and management.





Created an enchanting and interactive website catering to young explorers, providing a platform to showcase pictures and share stories.
Enhanced Frontend Skills: Strengthened proficiency in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript through project implementation.
Overcame layout optimization challenges for a responsive design and successfully implemented a dy- namic slideshow, showcasing adaptability and problem-solving skills.





Completed a Python project with Word Guessing, Adventure Game, and Weather Tool.
Developed comprehensive testing cases covering various functional aspects of the project to ensure stability and reliability.
Overcame challenges in API usage, learned game design principles, and enhanced the overall experience by improving API interactions and mastering Python syntax.










Guided and mentored a weekly cohort of 15+ students, nurturing a strong grasp of programming fundamentals and equipping them with practical problem-solving skills in Python, HTML, and CSS, while introducing valuable tools and techniques.






Awarded the BYU-Idaho Grant for the academic year 2023-2024.
